The generator has no idea what the enum is.  If you open your schema in swagger, that `importType` field doesn&#39;t exist.  So, Jackson is interpreting the type as a string.  When you try to map the string to the enum, Jackson doesn&#39;t know what to do.  Remember, the enum itself is not a String, so Jackson needs instruction.  Update your enum to use the `@JsonValue` as follows and it should work fine.

```java
public enum ImportType
{
  MRI(1, &quot;MRI&quot;);
  private final Integer code;
  private final String value;

  ImportType(int code, String value)
  {
    this.code = code;
    this.value = value;
  }

  public static ImportType getById(int id)
  {
    for (ImportType typeOfImport : ImportType.values()) {
      if (typeOfImport.code.equals(id)) {
        return typeOfImport;
      }
    }
    return null;
  }

  public int getCode()
  {
    return code;
  }

  @JsonValue
  public String getValue()
  {
    return value;
  }
}
```

You could also add a helper method with the `@JsonCreator` annotation, such as below.

```java
  @JsonCreator
  public static ImportType ofValue(String value)
