Regardless of the route you take though, I highly recommend creating a schema for the `FileImportInput` class and overriding it&#39;s TypeMapping in your configuration.  The primary purpose of the swagger interface that comes with openapi is to document your rest service.  As it is, your clients have no way of knowing what values are acceptable for the `ImportType` without you stating it in your description.

You can do this by creating the schema (possibly calling it `GeneratedFileImportInput`) and setting it to mimic your `abstract FileImportInput`, and then in your maven plugin, change the configuration for the `typeMappings` to have `GeneratedFileImportInput=FileImportInput` and `importMappings` to have `FileImportInput=my.package.of.FileImportInput`.  This will replace all generated occurances of the `GeneratedFileImportInput` with your version.

You can also take it a step further by adding the `GeneratedFileImportInput` to your `.openapi-generator-ignore` to ensure the file isn&#39;t generated at all.

